&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Airbnb was born in 2007 when two hosts welcomed three guests to their San Francisco home, and has since grown to over 5 million hosts who have welcomed over 2 billion guest arrivals in almost every country across the globe. Every day, hosts offer unique stays and experiences that make it possible for guests to connect with communities in a more authentic way.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Community You Will Join:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our mission at Marketing Technology is to provide a state-of-the-art platform and measurement capabilities to enable marketing and product teams to engage with our customers effectively. Everyday millions of Airbnb customers are reached via our streamlined platform over comprehensive channels, such as Email, Push, SMS, In-App Channels as well as external Ads Platforms (e.g., Google, Facebook, etc). We deliver substantial business impact by enabling numerous stakeholders across the company, including Marketing (Brand and Performance), Guest/Host, Policy, and more.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Difference You Will Make:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Senior Software Engineer on Marketing Technology’s Content Platform team, you’ll provide hands-on technical leadership to build a no-code or low-code platform to bring together a thoughtful user experience for Marketing to author, segment, and plan lifecycle management of communications on onsite (&lt;a href=&quot;http://airbnb.com/&quot;&gt;airbnb.com&lt;/a&gt;, in-app) and offsite (emails, push notification) channels.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You and your team will own the serving and hydration of billions of heavily personalized pieces of marketing content.&amp;nbsp; Knowing that any downtime in our systems results in a loss of trust from our customers and loss of revenue from our marketing channels, you will help own the quality and uptime of our systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll be working alongside with a team of talented software engineers to improve our usability of the platform of tools, reducing time-to-market for our internal teams, and develop technical strategic planning towards driving a best-in-class platform. You will also work closely with XFN partners like design, product and marketing stakeholders to dive deep to solving problems that have direct monetary impact on our business.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A Typical Day: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Senior Software Engineer on Content Platform, you will:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with cross-functional partners including product managers, designers and marketing managers to design and deliver high-quality products across multiple channels that directly contribute to Airbnb’s revenue.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead efforts to architect and build technology for serving marketing content to guests and hosts across Airbnb’s stack—including our web frontends, GraphQL API gateway &amp;amp; business logic layer, and storage layer.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Make heavy use of our mature DevAI stack to explore, build and verify your work.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Think user first: you might optimize user experience page performance by improving our rendering layer, or how we fan out and fetch data in the backend.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with customers to identify usability issues and proactively fix them.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build relationships with engineers in product orgs (e.g. Relevance, Stays, Experiences) and partner with them to support company-wide initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Expertise :&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;6+ years of experience in a hands-on software engineering role.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s and/or Master’s degree, preferably in CS, or equivalent experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technical leadership: hands on experience leading project teams, setting technical direction and strategy and mentoring engineers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated comfort in working in a fullstack environment—you might be a backend expert, but are happy building client components; or a client expert who is happy building efficient APIs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Passionate about efficiency, availability, technical quality and system quality.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Passion to level-up those around you through curiosity and fostering a collaborative and inclusive team environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience in defining product strategy and helping drive alignment with cross-functional leaders and stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication and collaboration skills with experience driving initiatives that span across teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;San Francisco Bay Area Location preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Bonus&lt;/em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If you’ve worked in and/or have opinions about the current state of Marketing Technology.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If you have demonstrable Agentic AI experience with production applications, or have explored enough in your spare time to be able to speak to it.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Location:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position is US - Remote Eligible. The role may include occasional work at an Airbnb office or attendance at offsites, as agreed to with your manager. While the position is Remote Eligible, you must live in a state where Airbnb, Inc. has a registered entity.&lt;a href=&quot;https://careers.airbnb.com/&quot;&gt; Click here&lt;/a&gt; for the up-to-date list of excluded states. This list is continuously evolving, so please check back with us if the state you live in is on the exclusion list. If your position is employed by another Airbnb entity, your recruiter will inform you what states you are eligible to work from.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Commitment To Inclusion &amp;amp; Belonging:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Airbnb is committed to working with the broadest talent pool possible. We believe diverse ideas foster innovation and engagement, and allow us to attract creatively-led people, and to develop the best products, services and solutions. All qualified individuals are encouraged to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We strive to also provide a disability inclusive application and interview process. If you are a candidate with a disability and require reasonable accommodation in order to submit an application, please contact us at: &lt;a href=&quot;mailto:reasonableaccommodations@airbnb.com&quot;&gt;reasonableaccommodations@airbnb.com&lt;/a&gt;. Please include your full name, the role you’re applying for and the accommodation necessary to assist you with the recruiting process.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We ask that you only reach out to us if you are a candidate whose disability prevents you from being able to complete our online application.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;How We&#39;ll Take Care of You:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Our job titles may span more than one career level. The actual base pay is dependent upon many factors, such as: training, transferable skills, work experience, business needs and market demands. The base pay range is subject to change and may be modified in the future. This role may also be eligible for bonus, equity, benefits, and Employee Travel Credits. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;title&quot;&gt;Pay Range&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-range&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;$196,000&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;divider&quot;&gt;&amp;mdash;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;$227,000 USD&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We&#39;re transforming the grocery industry&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;im&quot;&gt;At Instacart, we invite the world to share love through food because we believe everyone should have access to the food they love and more time to enjoy it together. Where others see a simple need for grocery delivery, we see exciting complexity and endless opportunity to serve the varied needs of our community. We work to deliver an essential service that customers rely on to get their groceries and household goods, while also offering safe and flexible earnings opportunities to Instacart Personal Shoppers.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Instacart has become a lifeline for millions of people, and we’re building the team to help push our shopping cart forward. If you’re ready to do the best work of your life, come join our table.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Instacart is a Flex First team &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There’s no one-size fits all approach to how we do our best work. Our employees have the flexibility to choose where they do their best work—whether it’s from home, an office, or your favorite coffee shop—while staying connected and building community through regular in-person events. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.instacart.careers/flex-first&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; data-saferedirecturl=&quot;https://www.google.com/url?q=https://instacart.careers/remote/&amp;amp;source=gmail&amp;amp;ust=1651869232122000&amp;amp;usg=AOvVaw37OlxP8hAKN7nq4YwHQH7e&quot;&gt;Learn more about our flexible approach to where we work.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3&gt;OVERVIEW&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Developer Experience team at Instacart is the force multiplier for our 1000+ engineers. We define and build the platforms, tools, and practices that enable Instacart engineers to ship high-quality software faster — from AI-powered code review to build infrastructure, developer onboarding, and local development environments. Our success is measured in developer velocity: how quickly an engineer can take an idea from concept to production.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Staff Software Engineer on Developer Experience, you will lead two of the pillars that Instacart engineering is built on: &lt;strong&gt;Bazel&lt;/strong&gt; (our build system) and &lt;strong&gt;Go&lt;/strong&gt; (one of our core backend languages). You will own the technical direction for how thousands of daily builds run and how our Go services are structured, from remote build execution and caching to the frameworks, libraries, and patterns Go engineers use every day. This is a hands-on technical leadership role. You&#39;ll write code, set architectural direction, and partner across the org to move engineering-wide metrics on build performance, CI reliability, and developer velocity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;About the Job&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the technical direction for Instacart&#39;s Bazel build system, including remote caching, remote build execution (RBE), build performance, and the developer-facing ergonomics of the build.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the technical direction for our Go platform, frameworks, standard libraries, service scaffolding, and patterns that Go engineers across Instacart depend on.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and drive multi-quarter initiatives that measurably improve build times, CI reliability, and the local development loop for engineers working in Bazel and Go.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the developer experience metrics for the systems you lead, define what &quot;good&quot; looks like, instrument it, and use the data to prioritize investment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with infrastructure, platform, and product engineering teams to roll out changes to the build system and Go platform with minimal disruption.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Set the technical bar for the systems you own on reliability, performance, upgrade cadence, and developer ergonomics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentor engineers in the team and the broader engineering org; grow the community of Bazel and Go experts at Instacart.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Represent the team in cross-org technical discussions on build, CI/CD, and backend platform direction.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;About You&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A hands-on technical leader who is equally comfortable in a Bazel BUILD file, a Go service, and a design doc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Metrics-driven, You use build times, cache hit rates, CI reliability, and developer feedback to guide where to invest.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A multiplier. You make the engineers around you more effective through mentorship, clear technical writing, and pragmatic guidance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable driving cross-team change. You can build consensus for a migration or a platform shift and see it through to adoption.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Minimum Qualifications&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10+ years of software development experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep, hands-on expertise with Bazel, including remote caching, remote build execution (RBE), and performance tuning of large build graphs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong production experience writing and operating Go services at scale, with a point of view on structuring large Go codebases (frameworks, dependency management, testing patterns, shared libraries).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track record of leading cross-team technical initiatives with measurable impact on developer velocity, build performance, or CI reliability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with cloud infrastructure (AWS preferred) and distributed systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong technical leadership, driving direction, mentoring engineers, and influencing without direct authority.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Preferred Qualifications&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s or Master&#39;s degree in Computer Science, Computer Engineering, or equivalent experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience migrating a large codebase or monorepo to Bazel, or evolving an existing Bazel setup through major upgrades.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience owning or contributing to a Go framework, standard library, or service scaffolding used by a large engineering org.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience defining and instrumenting developer productivity metrics (build times, cache hit rates, CI reliability, local dev loop).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience at high-growth companies operating developer infrastructure for large engineering organizations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
